Put oven rack in middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Cut 48 rounds from bread with 1 1/2-inch cutter. Toast rounds on a baking sheet until crisp, about 10 minutes. Cut 48 rounds from red peppers with 1 1/4-inch cutter. Reserve 48 almond slices for garnish, then chop remainder. Stir together cheese, parsley, zest, black pepper, and chopped almonds in a bowl. Put 1/4 teaspoon cheese mixture onto each toast, then top with a pepper round, pressing down lightly. Mound 1/4 teaspoon more cheese mixture onto each pepper round and garnish with an almond slice.